{"questionId":"33373907","questionHtml":"<p>The total surface area of the hollow cylinder is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>240</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>cm</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>Show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>360</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>45</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>240</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math></p>\n<p>attempt to solve their equation for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mi>h</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> (must isolate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mi>h</mi></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>240</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>10</mn><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>24</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>240</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></math> &nbsp; (or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>uses volume <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo></math> large cylinder&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo></math> small cylinder&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to substitute in for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mi>h</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>24</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>240</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>24</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math> &nbsp; OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>384</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>48</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>24</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>360</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>45</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[6 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33373907","referenceCode":"24N.1.SL.TZ2.9b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The total surface area of the hollow cylinder is 240π cm2. Show that V=360πr-45πr3.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, distance, midpoints"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}